Back-Channel Guide
1
Open your browser and navigate to: "https://IP_Data_Collector/". You can also use
the a4conf icon on the Data Collector desktop.
2
Click "Back-Channel" within the main menu.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 2
3
The "Topics" tab is a whitelist that allows the passage of MQTT messages only on
the listed topics. The passage is from Data Sender to Data Collector, via the back
channel, even with closed bidirectionality. You can click on the "+" icon to add a
new entry to the tab.
4
Enter the topic name in the "Topics" field of the new tab "Add new row".
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 3
5
Click the "Ok" button to create the new entry.
6
Click the "pencil" icon next to an existing entry to edit it, or the "red trash" icon to
delete it.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 4
7
Remember to click the "Save" button.
8
Move to "File names".
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 5
9
The "File names" tab is a whitelist that only allows the passage of files for the
filenames listed. The passage is from Data Sender to Data Collector, via the Back
Channel, even when bidirectionality is closed. You can click on the "+" icon to add a
new entry to the tab.
10
Enter the topic name in the "Topics" field of the new tab "Add new row".
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 6
11
Click the "Ok" button to create the new entry.
12
Click the "pencil" icon next to an existing entry to edit it, or the "red trash" icon to
delete it.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 7
13
Move to "JSON" to see the page configurations in JSON format. This section is
available in every admin page.
14
Click the "Apply" button to apply the new configurations.
